ing your advice using a PIN  your VMI ID number  and your SSN to log into PostView as a guest Please call 464 7157 or 464 7158 if you do not receive a letter  W 2 Statements Employees with VMI email addresses may give permission to receive their W 2 statements online through PostView  Payroll will notify employees by email when electronic copies are available  which is earlier than mailed copies  Under  Employee Profile   where advices are located  click on  W 2 Electronic Consent  to give permission  then under  W 2 Statements  to locate current and past W 2 statements which you may print and use for filing tax returns  Note that the forms have four copies on one page and must be cut apart if you need to attach a copy to your return  These copies are displayed in an IRS approved format  Employees without a VMI email address will have their W 2s mailed by 31 January of the following year  Payroll Office Payroll Home Access to Pay Info  Pay Schedule FAQs Payroll Staff VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 